  "default_info": {
    "title": "Lysis of nonnucleated red blood cells by cytotoxic T lymphocytes.",
    "abstract": "To establish the role of direct membrane damage in cytotoxic T lymphocytes (CTL)-mediated lysis we investigated whether CTL would be capable of lysing nonnucleated target cells. By antibody-mediated targeting we show that CTL are indeed capable of lysing sheep and human red blood cells.",
